{
  "stem": "33.1",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And all the Jewish people, not only from my town, but all the surrounding smaller towns, religious farms, what have you, were all concentrated in this section.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "The hostages were let out before we got-- we had to go into the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I remember the Jewish community was in charge to feed the hostages.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And twice a day, we would take food.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "There was a kitchen where they made the food.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And I guess we all contributed-- families who had a-- a member there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And all the youngsters, we wanted to take-- take the food in big containers.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "We took the food to this house where the hostages were, just to be able to maybe to see our fathers for a minute.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "They didn't really let them come out and talk to us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But what happened, somebody looked out from behind a corner, and then they knew that whose daughter, or son, whose-- we were a few always out there.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And then they would tell the hostage to come out just for a minute to see their daughter or their son.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And I remember my father, who was always very conscious about learning, and about, you know, school-- and I guess he was very proud of me, because I was a very good student.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "I was usually among the first three in my grade.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And I remember him asking me how-- what my grades were for high school graduation.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And when I told him it was all A's, I, you know, I could see he was happy about that.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "Anyway, we did get in the ghetto about middle of May.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And we could arrange ahead of time if we knew somebody who lived in that area to move in their house.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
